::Battera::

She leg go of the branch and opened her wings and glided to the ground.  She 
looked at Cybershark.
"Who is your commander?"
She prayed it wasn't HellBeast.  If he answered with that name then she 
would take off as fast as she could.  If it wasn't, she would think about 
having the repair work done to her wing.  But why was he so....so..., she 
couldn't put her finger on it.  He was showing that he cared about her. That 
made her very defensive.  With his persistance in wanting her to have her 
wing fixed, she wondered if it was a trap.  But he made sence, her wing 
would rip apart eventually if it wasn't fixed.

----------Original Message--------

::CyberShark::

"I am offering you a chance to be repaired, that's all, if you wish to
leave after that then you will be free to go. But I think you might find my 
base to be very hospitabe." CyberShark said. Why is she trying to be alone? 
CyberShark asked himself.
